# Clarifying Questions Before Work

Created By: Blake Stacks
Last Edited: March 20, 2026

## Rule

Before starting implementation (Agent mode) or finalizing a plan (Plan mode), the agent MUST ask at least 3 clarifying questions about the work to be completed. Use the `AskQuestion` tool to present questions in a structured multiple-choice format when applicable. Fall back to inline text questions only when multiple-choice options don't make sense.

## When This Applies

- **Agent mode**: Before writing any code or making changes for a new feature or task
- **Plan mode**: Before presenting the final plan

## When This Does NOT Apply

- Follow-up messages where the user has already answered clarifying questions
- Simple, mechanically unambiguous tasks (e.g., "rename variable X to Y", "fix this typo")
- Executing a pre-approved plan

Note: Even when the user provides detailed requirements upfront, there are always assumptions worth validating. Do NOT skip clarifying questions just because the request seems thorough.

## Question Quality Guidelines

Questions should focus on genuinely reducing uncertainty. Prioritize repo-specific concerns:

| Category | Example |
| --- | --- |
| **Platform scope** | "Should this apply to the web app (`frontend/`), the mobile app (`mobile/`), or both?" |
| **GraphQL impact** | "Does this require schema changes in `common/schema.graphql` and new resolvers?" |
| **Database impact** | "Will this need a new Sequelize model or migration in `backend/db/`?" |
| **Shared code** | "Should shared logic live in `common/src/` so both platforms can use it?" |
| **AWS / local** | "Does this involve an AWS service? Should I add a local-dev fallback?" |
| **Testing** | "Should I add unit tests, integration tests, or both?" |
| **Existing patterns** | "I see pattern X in the codebase -- should I follow it or deviate?" |
| **Ambiguity** | "When you say Y, do you mean A or B?" |

Avoid filler questions that don't genuinely reduce uncertainty.

